 and Carousel if useful. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Use Aceternity-inspired patterns such as bento grids, spotlight backgrounds, moving borders, sticky reveals, timelines, and card stacks by implementing lightweight local components with current Tailwind/CSS, not by installing heavy dependencies. Add SVG/CSS graphics and abstract visual panels. No external image URLs, no copyrighted images, no fake screenshots, no fake client logos. All components must be responsive, accessible, respect reduced motion, and scoped so they do not alter the landing page. Run lint/build. Final response must confirm landing page untouched.\"\n 25 |   },\n 26 |   {\n 27 |     \"id\": \"03-homepage-hero-preservation-and-metrics\",\n 28 |     \"title\": \"Verify approved hero and required metrics\",\n 29 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 30 |     \"target\": \"landing hero\",\n 31 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 32 |     \"prompt\": \"Inspect the landing hero only. Preserve the approved hero UI exactly, especially the right-side video placement, hero layout, spacing, typography, video container, overlay, and responsive behavior. Do not redesign the hero. Verify the hero contains the required headline: Building the World's First AI-Native Enterprise Transformation Company. Verify the subheading: Combining Agentic AI, Knowledge Graphs, Industry Platforms, Talent Cloud, and Managed AI Operations into a single transformation ecosystem. Verify primary CTA: Generate My Enterprise AI Blueprint. Verify secondary CTA: Experience GFF AI Live. Add or preserve hero metrics in the least intrusive existing style: 500+ AI Use Cases, 20+ Industries, Global Delivery Model, Agent Factory, Knowledge Graph Factory, AI Academy. Do not create fake metrics. Do not replace the video with a dashboard or foundry visual. Run lint/build. Final response must confirm hero video placement untouched.\"\n 33 |   },\n 34 |   {\n 35 |     \"id\": \"04-homepage-enterprise-quick-search\",\n 36 |     \"title\": \"Restore or build Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search\",\n 37 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 38 |     \"target\": \"Enterprise Quick Search after hero\",\n 39 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 40 |     \"prompt\": \"Add or restore Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search immediately after the approved hero. This section is mandatory. Preserve the approved hero and all existing landing styles. Build a local, frontend-only AI concierge style search that searches static local content across Industries, Capabilities, Platforms, Build With GFF tools, Resources, and Company pages. Include clickable example searches: Build AI for Banking, Create University AI Lab, Insurance AI, Mining AI, Retail AI, Build AI GCC. Results must appear instantly when typing or clicking examples. Each result must show title, category, short description, and route link. No API calls. No backend. No fake data. Design must be premium, clean, Apple-like, and consistent with the current landing theme. Use subtle Framer Motion or CSS transitions if available. Avoid box-inside-box clutter, excessive pills, badge soup, and neon overload. Mobile must be excellent. Acceptance: section appears after hero, search works locally, examples work, empty state is polished, links resolve, build passes.\"\n 41 |   },\n 42 |   {\n 43 |     \"id\": \"05-homepage-garage-foundry-factory-journey\",\n 44 |     \"title\": \"Complete Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n 45 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 46 |     \"target\": \"Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n 47 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 48 |     \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the homepage transformation journey. It must include Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, Optimize, and Scale. Use the existing approved landing section if one already maps to this. Do not create duplicates. Do not redesign approved sections unnecessarily. Each step should have a concise description, outcome, and route link: Garage /platforms/garage, Foundry /platforms/foundry, Factory /platforms/factory, Operate /capabilities/operations or /platforms/control-center, Optimize /platforms/control-center, Scale /platforms/factory. UI should feel premium, like an enterprise operating model timeline, with subtle motion and responsive vertical mobile layout. Avoid visual clutter. Run lint/build.\"\n 49 |   },\n 50 |   {\n 51 |     \"id\": \"06-homepage-what-we-build\",\n 52 |     \"title\": \"Complete What We Build section\",\n 53 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 54 |     \"target\": \"What We Build capabilities section\",\n 55 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 56 |     \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the homepage What We Build section. It must include these required cards: AI Strategy, AI Engineering, Agentic AI, AI Governance, AI Labs, AI Factory, AI Marketplace, AI Operations. Use existing approved card/grid design if present. Do not duplicate an existing capabilities section. Add links: AI Strategy /capabilities/strategy, AI Engineering /capabilities/engineering, Agentic AI /capabilities/agents, AI Governance /capabilities/governance, AI Labs /capabilities/labs, AI Factory /platforms/factory or /capabilities/operations, AI Marketplace /platforms/marketplace, AI Operations /capabilities/operations. Include secondary references where natural: Knowledge Graph, Data Platforms, Digital Twins, University Platforms, Managed Services. Design must be elegant, expensive, responsive, and not a generic card dump. Use subtle hover and reveal animations. No fake claims. Run lint/build.\"\n 57 |   },\n 58 |   {\n 59 |     \"id\": \"07-homepage-interactive-experience\",\n 60 |     \"title\": \"Complete Interactive Experience section\",\n 61 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 62 |     \"target\": \"Interactive Experience tools section\",\n 63 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 64 |     \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the Interactive Experience section on the homepage. It must include Talk to Agent, Blueprint Generator, AI Readiness, ROI Calculator, Marketplace, and Foundry Studio. Link to /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /platforms/marketplace or /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio or /platforms/foundry. If an existing BuildAIEnterpriseSection or similar approved section exists, update it minimally instead of replacing it. The design should feel like premium self-service enterprise tools, with tasteful cards or tabs, subtle motion, frontend-only preview behavior, no real API calls, and no fake outputs. Avoid nested boxes and excessive badges. Run lint/build.\"\n 65 |   },\n 66 |   {\n 67 |     \"id\": \"08-homepage-global-presence\",\n 68 |     \"title\": \"Add Global Presence section\",\n 69 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 70 |     \"target\": \"Global Presence\",\n 71 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 72 |     \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the Global Presence section on the homepage. Include Singapore as Global Headquarters, London UK as Client Innovation Centre or Client Center, India as AI Engineering Factory or Build Shop, and future regions Australia, Middle East, USA. Use an existing world map component if available. If not, create a lightweight SVG/CSS global hub visual or premium region grid. Do not add a heavy 3D globe dependency. Do not invent office addresses. Do not invent fake headcount unless already approved in content. Make the UI clean, cinematic, enterprise-grade, responsive, and aligned with landing theme. Add subtle motion or hover states. Run lint/build.\"\n 73 |   },\n 74 |   {\n 75 |     \"id\": \"09-homepage-client-success\",\n 76 |     \"title\": \"Add Client Success section\",\n 77 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 78 |     \"target\": \"Client Success\",\n 79 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 80 |     \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the homepage Client Success section. Required elements: Case Studies, Video, Architecture, Business Outcomes. Use only anonymized representative patterns, never fake clients or fake logos. Representative patterns may include Global Banking Transformation, Healthcare Knowledge Operations, Manufacturing AI Factory, Retail Agent Operations. Label them as representative patterns. No fake numbers, no fake ROI, no fake customer names. Create a premium design with tabs, carousel, or narrative cards if appropriate. Include an architecture preview panel and outcome themes such as faster decision making, reduced manual effort, better knowledge access, improved compliance workflows, and improved employee experience. Mobile friendly. Run lint/build.\"\n 81 |   },\n 82 |   {\n 83 |     \"id\": \"10-homepage-live-dashboard\",\n 84 |     \"title\": \"Add Live Dashboard preview section\",\n 85 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 86 |     \"target\": \"Live Dashboard\",\n 87 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 88 |     \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the homepage Live Dashboard section. Required labels: Active Clients, Agents Running, AI Projects, Countries, Industries, Agent Health, Delivery, Spend, Adoption, Governance. Do not invent precise values. You may use only approved values such as 500+ AI Use Cases and 20+ Industries where appropriate. Other dashboard items must be label-only states such as Monitoring-ready, Connected in Control Center, Frontend preview, or Governance-ready. Design should feel like a premium enterprise AI operations control center, not a crypto dashboard. Use subtle animated status lines, charts without fake data, and clean dashboard panels. No backend, no real-time claims. Responsive and accessible. Run lint/build.\"\n 89 |   },\n 90 |   {\n 91 |     \"id\": \"11-homepage-latest-research\",\n 92 |     \"title\": \"Add Latest Research section\",\n 93 |     \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n 94 |     \"target\": \"Latest Research\",\n 95 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n 96 |     \"prompt\": \"Add or restore the homepage Latest Research section. Include Articles, Videos, Podcasts, Whitepapers, plus links to Blog, Research, Case Studies, Architecture Library, Webinars, Events, Developer Docs, Downloads, Reports, Newsroom, Thought Leadership, and Patterns of Intelligence routes where they exist. Do not invent article titles with fake authors, fake dates, fake PDFs, or fake downloads. Use category cards, editorial visuals, research library previews, and coming-soon states. Design should feel like a premium research and intelligence library. Mobile friendly. Run lint/build.\"\n 97 |   },\n 98 |   {\n 99 |     \"id\": \"12-blueprint-generator-compliance\",\n100 |     \"title\": \"Verify and fix Blueprint Generator scoring\",\n101 |     \"scope\": \"functionality\",\n102 |     \"target\": \"Blueprint Generator\",\n103 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n104 |     \"prompt\": \"Verify and fix the Blueprint Generator. It must be frontend-only and may appear on homepage and /build/blueprint. It must include title: Get Your Enterprise AI Blueprint in 60 Seconds. Required inputs: Industry, Company Size, Top Priorities with max 3 selection, AI Journey, Data Readiness, Leadership Commitment, Biggest Challenge, Email, OTP placeholder. Optional: Budget and Geography. It must not send real OTP or call backend. Formula: Blueprint Score = 0.20(AI Maturity)+0.25(Business Need)+0.20(Data Readiness)+0.20(Process Complexity)+0.15(Transformation Readiness). Scoring: No AI 10, Exploring AI 30, Running Pilots 60, Scaling AI 85, AI-Driven Enterprise or AI-Native 100. Business Need: Cost Reduction 20, Productivity 20, Customer Experience 15, Revenue Growth 15, Compliance 10, AI Transformation 20, Automate Processes 20, capped at 100. Data Readiness: Highly fragmented 20, Partially connected 50, Mostly integrated 75, Fully integrated 100. Process Complexity: <100 20, 100-1000 50, 1000-10000 80, 10000+ 100. Transformation Readiness: Not Discussed 20, Exploring 50, Budget Approved 80, Executive Mandate 100. Categories: 0-25 AI Beginner, 26-50 AI Explorer, 51-70 AI Adopter, 71-85 AI Transformer, 86-100 AI-Native Leader. Test example Banking, 15000 employees, Scaling AI, Productivity + Cost Reduction + Compliance, Mostly Integrated Data, Budget Approved must display 87/100. Required outputs: AI Readiness Score, Top 5 Recommended AI Opportunities, Recommended GFF AI Solution, Expected Business Impact, 90-Day Roadmap. Label impacts as expected/modelled, not guaranteed. Run lint/build.\"\n105 |   },\n106 |   {\n107 |     \"id\": \"13-nav-footer-and-sitemap-completion\",\n108 |     \"title\": \"Complete navigation footer and sitemap links\",\n109 |     \"scope\": \"navigation-footer\",\n110 |     \"target\": \"Header Footer Sitemap\",\n111 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n112 |     \"prompt\": \"Verify and complete the public navigation, footer, and sitemap route links. Do not redesign header or footer. Keep the current approved visual style. Header must include HOME, WHY GFF AI, CAPABILITIES, INDUSTRIES, PLATFORMS, BUILD WITH GFF, RESOURCES, COMPANY, CONTACT, CLIENT LOGIN. Footer must include Quick Links, Solutions, Industries, Platforms, Company, Legal, Newsletter where current layout supports it. Required legal/support links: Privacy, NDA, Terms, Investor Relations, Client Portal. All hrefs must resolve to explicit pages. Do not use slug routing. Do not create fake newsletter sending; frontend-only state only. Run lint/build.\"\n113 |   },\n114 |   {\n115 |     \"id\": \"14-command-center\",\n116 |     \"title\": \"Command Center CmdK CtrlK\",\n117 |     \"scope\": \"functionality\",\n118 |     \"target\": \"Command Center\",\n119 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n120 |     \"prompt\": \"Verify or implement a frontend-only Command Center. It should open with Cmd+K on Mac and Ctrl+K on Windows/Linux. Commands: Talk to Agent /build/talk, Generate Blueprint /build/blueprint, Estimate ROI /build/roi, Launch Sandbox /build/sandbox, Book Workshop /contact. It must be keyboard accessible, have focus handling, work on desktop, and have a safe mobile trigger if needed. Use existing header or global layout mounting without redesigning the header or landing page. No API calls. Use premium modal/command UI inspired by modern command palettes and Aceternity-style effects if lightweight. Run lint/build.\"\n121 |   },\n122 |   {\n123 |     \"id\": \"15-frontend-only-placeholder-safety\",\n124 |     \"title\": \"Ensure frontend-only placeholders\",\n125 |     \"scope\": \"frontend-safety\",\n126 |     \"target\": \"forms and interactive tools\",\n127 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n128 |     \"prompt\": \"Audit and fix all forms and interactive tools to be frontend-only placeholders. Check Contact, Newsletter, Portal login, Control Center, Talk to Agent, Blueprint, Assessment, ROI, Sandbox, Proposal Builder, Marketplace, Foundry Studio. No real API calls, no auth, no AWS, no OTP sending, no real email sending, no database calls, no export file generation, no env dependency. If an existing legacy API route exists, do not use it from the public frontend. Placeholder copy must clearly say backend/FastAPI integration will come later only where appropriate. Run grep/search for fetch, axios, app/api calls, localhost, NEXT_PUBLIC_API, AWS, Cognito, SES, S3. Fix violations only. Run lint/build.\"\n129 |   },\n130 |   {\n131 |     \"id\": \"16-why-gff-ai-design-family\",\n132 |     \"title\": \"Design Why GFF AI page family\",\n133 |     \"scope\": \"page-family-design\",\n134 |     \"target\": \"Why GFF AI explicit pages\",\n135 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n136 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /why-gff-ai and all Why GFF AI subpages into a premium executive narrative design family. Do not touch the landing page. Pages: /why-gff-ai, /why-gff-ai/mission, /why-gff-ai/vision, /why-gff-ai/garage-foundry-factory, /why-gff-ai/operating-model, /why-gff-ai/leadership, /why-gff-ai/global-model, /why-gff-ai/technology-philosophy, /why-gff-ai/differentiator. Design mood: strategic, editorial, boardroom-level, 